					<div id="aboutHopeHallDiv">
						<br>
				      <p class="" id="abouthopeHallText"><span style="font-size:24px; font-family:Gabriola";>
				          &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The Redeemed Christian Church Of God, Rccg Hopehall, 221, Apapa Road is a place where hope is truly restored and 
				          champions raised. A parish with a mandate to bring the gospel of Christ to the world in these last days.
				          We believe that our God is still in the business of bringing hope to the hopeless and lifting up people from the dung 
				          hill of life to the mountain top of excellence and that is what we stand for. Experience God in your life as you worship with us.
				          <br>
				          <span style="font-size:27px; font-weight:600; font-family:Gabriola; text-align:center;">Our Pastors</span>
				          <br>
				          &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp When Hope Hall started in 1996 with Pastor Gbenga Olaiwola as the Parish Pastor, Pastor Shaff Durojaiye worked  
				          closely with him as his assistant. 
				          Pastor Olaiwola however left for an opportunity to serve the nations in the United States of America. He left Pastor Durojaiye in
				           the acting capacity, to run the parish through the rest of 1997 until after the 1998 RCCG Convention when he was confirmed as the parish pastor. 
				          The vision for the nations continued on the foundation of building people for the work of the Lord. The interest was to encourage 
				          everyone who was interested, to work in the Lord’s Vineyard. Training remained key and leadership through service was held in high importance. 
				          Pastor Shaff Durojaiye became the parish pastor effectively in 1998 and remained in that capacity for seven years, until 2005. He left for a career
				           opportunity abroad as a medical doctor. With the talks about moving out to the nations, he felt it was still an opportunity to carry on with the 
				           ministry work in other places away from home.  Since there would not be a void in God’s work, he asked Pastor Demola Adesanya, one of those who had 
				           worked with him for a long time, to continue to manage the affairs of the Church while he was away. Pastor Adesanya continued to hold forth until he
				          was made the Parish Pastor officially in 2008. Pastor Supo Oluwasakin resumed in Hope Hall as the Parish Pastor on September 5, 2010. At that time, 
				          the Church held its services at Classicus Arena, a place that was improvised following the road construction which affected its original location. 
				          The Church continued to be there for another 18 months because of challenges of getting a new place. It eventually opted for the choice of a property 
				          on a long lease, rather than continue to remain at the Arena. The Church was finally able to get a property on 221, Apapa Road, where it moved to 
				          in August 2011. The property was got on a seven years lease agreement, with the hope of acquiring a permanent place for the Church after the period of lease.
				          Rccg Hope hall, 221 Apapa road, Lagos, Nigeria - a place where hope is restored and champions raised.

				        </span></p>
